casebody.data:
WILLIAM H. RAHE v. STATE OF MARYLAND [No. 25,

October Term, 1938.]

Decided October 28th, 1938. *692The causes were argued before Bond, C. J., Urner, Offutt, Parke, Mitchell, Shehan, and Johnson, JJ. Robert B. Elliott, for the appellant. Herbert R. O’Conor, Attorney General, Hilary W. Gans, Deputy Attorney General, and William H. Maynard, Deputy State’s Attorney for Baltimore City, submitting on brief for the State. Urner, J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court.
